{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change from \u201cfirst past the post\u201d to \u201cmixed member proportional representation\u201d",
        "additional_details": "https://youtu.be/QT0I-sdoSXU\r\n\r\nMMP\r\nEach party\u2019s representation in Parliament is determined by their percentage of the nationwide party vote \u2013 MPs from the party list are added to the electorate MPs to bring each party up to the same percentage of seats in Parliament.\r\n\r\nFPP\r\nCandidates don\u2019t need more than 50 percent of the vote to win an electorate seat, just more than their closest opponent.\r\n\r\nMMP is a fairer representation of its voters in parliament, as  FPP only allows for a 2 party state.",
        "background": "Mixed Member Proportional (MMP)\r\nVoters have two votes, one for their electorate MP and one for their preferred political party.\r\n\r\nFirst Past the Post (FPP)\r\nThere is no party vote, and the representation each party has in Parliament is determined by how successful their electorate candidates are.",
